      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLEAR APPROVAL (1) settled back and picked up in great style, beaten just 0.6 lengths over 1200m at Ascot on debut. He'd trialled well, and the blinkers go straight on. Keeps Chris Parnham and will prove tough to beat. SAINTS 'N' SINNERS (5) resumed in the same race and hit the line well beaten 1.4L. She may get closer today. TIGERLAND (2) made decent improvement, beaten a nose over 1200m at Pinjarra. Started well out of the market, but dug deep, and the longer sprint will suit. On that effort, he has to be considered. PLAYING SOLO (3) had trialled well but didn't manage the 13 gate at Belmont on debut ($11sp).  Maps well here, and the gun jockey sticks aboard. Has the blinkers applied today and sharp improvement is on the cards.",
